<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<chapter xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0" xml:id="ivy.samplechapter">
    <info>
        <title>Sample Chapter</title>
    </info>
    <sect1 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.bookorganisation">
        <title>Organisation of the book</title>
        <para>The xml file <filename>ivy4DesignerGuide.xml</filename> is the index file of the
                <emphasis role="bold">book</emphasis>. Each <emphasis role="bold">chapter</emphasis>
            is provided in a separate file that is included in that book. A <emphasis role="bold"
                >chapter</emphasis> may have up to two sublevels. These sections and subsections are
            depicted by <emphasis role="bold">sect1</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold"
            >sect2</emphasis> elements.</para>
        <para>Chapters, sections and subsections should have an <emphasis role="bold"
            >xml:id</emphasis> attribute that will be used for cross-reference links within the
            book. The id should follow the pattern:
            <replaceable>ivy.chapterid.sectionid</replaceable>
        </para>
        <para>File mychapter.xml:</para>
        <screen>
         chapter    xmls:id="ivy.mychapter"
             
             sect1    xmls:id="ivy.mychapter.sectionX"
                 
                 sect2    xmls:id="ivy.mychapter.sectionN"
                 sect2    xmls:id="ivy.mychapter.sectionU"
             
             sect1    xmls:id="ivy.mychapter.sectionK"
                 
                 sect2    xmls:id="ivy.mychapter.sectionE"
        </screen>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.convention">
        <title>Conventions to be used </title>
        <para>This section covers the conventions used in our book.</para>
        <sect2 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.typo">
            <title>Typographic Conventions</title>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><code>Constant width</code></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Used to indicate source code: e.g. Java or IvyScript class names,
                            properties or methods. In the docbook xml you have to use the
                            &lt;code>&lt;/code> tag.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><emphasis role="italic">Italics</emphasis></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Used to introduce first-time used expressions, URL’s, email addresses,
                            filenames and directory paths. Also used for names of Roles. In docbook
                            you have to use the following tags: <variablelist>
                                <varlistentry>
                                    <term><emphasis role="italic">first timer</emphasis></term>
                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>&lt;emphasis role="italic"><emphasis role="italic"
                                                >first timer</emphasis>&lt;emphasis></para>
                                    </listitem>
                                </varlistentry>
                                <varlistentry>
                                    <term><uri>URL</uri></term>
                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>&lt;uri><uri>URL</uri>&lt;/uri></para>
                                    </listitem>
                                </varlistentry>
                                <varlistentry>
                                    <term><filename>filename, directory</filename></term>
                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>&lt;filename><filename>filename</filename>&lt;/filename></para>
                                    </listitem>
                                </varlistentry>
                            </variablelist></para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>this is <emphasis role="bold">important</emphasis></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The element <emphasis role="bold">emphasis</emphasis> is used to
                            highlight terms in a text</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><command>this is a command</command></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>A <emphasis role="bold">command</emphasis> element is used for
                            commands, command output, and options</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><replaceable>ivy Engine</replaceable></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>A <emphasis role="bold">replacable</emphasis> element is used for
                            replaceable items in code and text</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
            <sect3>
                <title>Examples:</title>
                <para>Given that a valid format is ensured, you can access the value of a
                        <code>RDatePicker</code> from the specialized attributes
                    <code>valueAsDate</code>. Note that the return value is a e.g.
                        <code>Date.INVALID</code> if the user input does not represent a valid
                    value. </para>
                <para>A combo box generates an <emphasis role="italic">Action</emphasis> event if an
                    option is selected. </para>
                <para>If the box has not been checked also anonymous users (which own the <emphasis
                        role="italic">Everybody</emphasis> role by default) may start the process.
                </para>
            </sect3>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.icons">
            <title>Icons</title>
            <note>
                <para>The <emphasis role="bold">note</emphasis> designates a note relating to the
                    surrounding text.</para>
            </note>
            <tip>
                <para>The <emphasis role="bold">tip</emphasis> designates a helpful tip relating to
                    the surrounding text.</para>
            </tip>
            <warning>
                <para>The <emphasis role="bold">warning</emphasis> designates a warning relating to
                    the surrounding text.</para>
            </warning>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.screen">
            <title>Screen</title>
            <para>Use a <emphasis role="bold">screen</emphasis> to show keybord input. e.g. script
                samples</para>
            <screen>
out.x=in.y;
        </screen>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.sidebar">
            <title>Sidebar</title>
            <sidebar xml:id="ivy.sidebar-1">
                <title>Sidebar</title>
                <para>In a <emphasis role="bold">sidebar</emphasis> you can give some background
                    information ...</para>
            </sidebar>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.links">
        <title>Links</title>
        <para><link linkend="ivy.samplechapter.icons">See this ! </link>This is a cross-reference
                <emphasis role="bold">link</emphasis> to an item in the book (section, chapter,
            figure ..) adressed by its id</para>
        <para><link xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="http://www.xml.com">click
                hier !</link> A <emphasis role="bold">link</emphasis> to any url in the www</para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.images">
        <title>Images</title>
        <para>This is an image inserted using the <emphasis role="bold">imagedata</emphasis>
            elements:</para>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/go.gif"/></imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>Put the image in a <emphasis role="bold">figure</emphasis> element, give it a
                <emphasis role="bold">title</emphasis> and an id. The figure will appear in the
                <emphasis role="bold">List of Figures</emphasis></para>
        <figure xmlns:id="samplechapter.images.figure1">
            <title>Lake in Fagaras</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="images/lake.jpeg" scale="50"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.lists">
        <title>Lists</title>
        <para>This is an <emphasis role="bold">itemizedlist</emphasis></para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <link xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="http://www.xml.com"
                        >http://www.xml.com</link>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <link xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="http://www.xml.org"
                        >http://www.xml.org</link>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <link xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="http://www.w3c.org"
                        >http://www.w3c.org</link>
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>This is a <emphasis role="bold">variablelist</emphasis>
        </para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Constructor: <code>public TemplateMergeField(String mergeFieldName, String mergeFieldValue)</code></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The file is unchanged in the working directory, and no changes to that
                        file have been committed to the repository since its working revision. An
                            <command>svn commit</command> of the file will do nothing, and an
                            <command>svn update</command> of the file will do nothing.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Field mergeFieldName</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The file has been changed in the working directory, and no changes to that
                        file have been committed to the repository since you last updated. There are
                        local changes that have not been committed to the repository, thus an
                            <command>svn commit</command> of the file will succeed in publishing
                        your changes, and an <command>svn update</command> of the file will do
                        nothing.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
        <para>This is an <emphasis role="bold">orderedlist</emphasis>:</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para> red </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para> green </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para> blue </para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.tables">
        <title>Tables</title>
        <sect2 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.htmltable">
            <title>Docbook 5 supports HTML tables</title>
            <para>The table should have a caption that will appear in the<emphasis role="bold"> List
                    of Tables</emphasis></para>
            <table frame="border">
                <caption>HTML Table</caption>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th align="left">Person Name</th>
                        <th align="left">Age</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Jane</td>
                        <td>26</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Bart </td>
                        <td>24</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Alexander</td>
                        <td>22</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td colspan="2">
                            <emphasis role="italic">They are all students of the computer science
                                department</emphasis>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 xml:id="ivy.samplechapter.docbooktable">
            <title>Docbook has special table elements </title>
            <para>The table must have a title that will appear in the<emphasis role="bold"> List of
                    Tables</emphasis></para>
            <table>
                <title>Docbook table </title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Schema</entry>
                            <entry>Access method</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry><literal>file:///</literal></entry>
                            <entry>Direct repository access (on local disk)</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry><literal>http://</literal></entry>
                            <entry>Access via WebDAV protocol to Subversion-aware Apache
                            server</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry><literal>https://</literal></entry>
                            <entry>Same as <literal>http://</literal>, but with SSL
                            encryption.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry><literal>svn://</literal></entry>
                            <entry>Access via custom protocol to an <literal>svnserve</literal>
                                server</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry><literal>svn+ssh://</literal></entry>
                            <entry>Same as <literal>svn://</literal>, but through an SSH
                            tunnel.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
</chapter>
